# ── Rust / Cargo ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
/target/
**/*.rs.bk
*.profraw

# moosedev is a BINARY application (the MCP server), so Cargo.lock IS committed
# for reproducible builds — the oxigraph-trivyn fork is pinned by git rev and we
# build offline against it. (The sibling `moose` *library* ignores Cargo.lock;
# we intentionally diverge. Do NOT add Cargo.lock to this file.)

# ── Runtime data — generated, never source ────────────────────────────────
# The durable project KG (persistent oxigraph / rocksdb store) and MOOSE's
# SQLite session DB are created at runtime. Keep all runtime state under /data/
# (MOOSE's SessionDb also defaults to sqlite:./data/moose_sessions.db).
/data/

# Live dogfood store — MOOSEDEV_DATA_DIR for the self-hosted MCP server.
/.moosedev/

# Transient SQLite sidecars — safe to ignore even when a .db is intentionally
# committed (e.g. the precomputed ontology-vector store used by alignment).
*.db-shm
*.db-wal
*.sqlite-shm
*.sqlite-wal

# NOTE: shipped precomputed ontology vectors (the alignment VecStore) are a
# committed / git-lfs artifact — keep them OUT of /data/ so they aren't ignored.

# ── Local config & secrets ────────────────────────────────────────────────
# LlmClient is configured via env (base_url / api_key / model). Never commit keys.
.env
.env.*
!.env.example

# Agent client local state. Repo-scoped MCP config is intentionally checked in
# via `.mcp.json` (Claude) and `.codex/config.toml` (Codex).
.claude/settings.local.json

# ── Editor & OS noise ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.DS_Store
*.swp
*.swo
*~
.idea/
.vscode/

# ── Logs ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
*.log

# --- UI -------------------------------------------------------------------
ui/node_modules/
ui/dist/
